# VeloIQ model authoring

## Required pattern

```python
from typing import Optional
from veloiq_framework import TimestampedModel


class MyModel(TimestampedModel, table=True):
    __tablename__ = "my_model"

    name: str
    description: Optional[str] = None
```

## Rules

- Always extend `TimestampedModel` — never `SQLModel` directly
- `__tablename__` must be snake_case; never use the `safem_` prefix
- After any change here, run `veloiq generate` then `veloiq db upgrade`
- Do not add endpoints here — use `custom_api.py` for custom logic
- Field types must be valid SQLModel/SQLAlchemy types; use `Optional[T]` for nullable columns

## Relationships

Use `jm_relationship` from `veloiq_framework` — **never** `relationship()` from SQLAlchemy or `Relationship` from SQLModel.

```python
from typing import TYPE_CHECKING, List, Optional
from sqlmodel import Field
from veloiq_framework import TimestampedModel, jm_relationship

if TYPE_CHECKING:
    from app.modules.other.models import OtherModel
    from app.modules.items.models import Item

class MyModel(TimestampedModel, table=True):
    __tablename__ = "my_model"

    # FK column (separate from the relationship)
    other_id: Optional[int] = Field(default=None, foreign_key="other.id")

    # Many-to-one
    other: Optional["OtherModel"] = jm_relationship(back_populates="my_models")

    # One-to-many
    items: List["Item"] = jm_relationship(back_populates="my_model")

    # Self-referential
    parent_id: Optional[int] = Field(default=None, foreign_key="my_model.id")
    children: List["MyModel"] = jm_relationship(
        back_populates="parent",
        sa_relationship_kwargs={"foreign_keys": "[MyModel.parent_id]"},
    )
    parent: Optional["MyModel"] = jm_relationship(
        back_populates="children",
        sa_relationship_kwargs={
            "foreign_keys": "[MyModel.parent_id]",
            "remote_side": "[MyModel.id]",
        },
    )
```

- Always guard cross-module imports with `if TYPE_CHECKING`
- Self-referential relationships require `sa_relationship_kwargs={"foreign_keys": [...]}` on both sides
- **Never add `from __future__ import annotations`** — it breaks SQLModel relationship resolution
